place.name: WOOD DALLING
place.gazetteerText: WOOD-DALLING, a parish, with a village, in Aylsham district, Norfolk; 7½ miles ENE of Elmham r. station. Post town, Reepham, under Norwich. Acres, 2,444. Real property, £4,138. Pop., 508. Houses, 116. The property is subdivided. The living is a vicarage, annexed to Swannington. The church is ancient but good. There are Independent and Primitive Methodist chapels, a national school, and charities £7. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
